2. Content Details for Each Page

Homepage (index.html)
This page is basically the intro to everything. I’ll explain what the site is about and what I learned this semester. It’ll also have links to all the other pages so it’s easy to click around.

Using the Code Editor (code-editor.html)
Here I’ll talk about the code editor I used (like VS Code) and how it helped me. I’ll include things like features, shortcuts, and how I used it for my projects.

HTML Semantic Elements (semantic-html.html)
This page will go over semantic HTML tags like header, section, and footer. I’ll explain what they do and why they make websites more organized and easier to read.

CSS Layout & Responsive Design (css-layout.html)
On this page I’ll explain how I used CSS to design my pages. I’ll talk about layouts like Flexbox/Grid and how I made my site look good on phones and computers.

Accessibility (accessibility.html)
This page is about making websites easier for everyone to use. I’ll include things like alt text, headings, and using colors that are easy to see.

Ethical Issues (ethics.html)
Here I’ll talk about important topics like privacy and being fair when making websites. It’s about doing the right thing as a web developer.

Code Validation (validation.html)
This page will show how I checked my code for errors. I’ll explain how I fixed problems and made sure everything worked correctly.

Using AI (ChatGPT) (ai.html)
This page will explain how I used AI tools like ChatGPT during the semester. I’ll show how it helped me understand things better and solve problems faster.

